text: Two teenage misfits meet at Camp Crystal Lake, in New Jersey near where four people died 15 years ago under mysterious circumstances while working as counselors there when they were teenagers.
Years later, one survivor Jason Voorhee has become a hulking deformed brute with an IQ equal to that of a toddler.
A year after his mother's death at the hands of randy young camp staffers, he sets himself on a homicidal spree to avenge her and everyone who mocks him by wearing the nickname 'Puny'.
And it doesn't stop there, because nowadays, he will kill anyone who trespasses into his turf out in a nearby forest (including the newly arrived camp leaders).

He is so relentless in killing everybody inside Camp Crystal Lake, whether in any of its building or its surrounding woods or water area outside camp perimeter, that some people start wondering what motivates him." - "Friday The Thirteenth", Toby Emmerich Production Company, April 9th.
